I remember praying for times like this.. everything I sacrificed to get here. It’s a surreal feeling, I don’t think words can express how I feel right now. I just want to start by saying THANK YOU to each one of my supporters, thank you to my clients that forever have my back and I will always have theirs. We’re more then clients at this point. We’re a family.

Entering my 3rd year in real estate, I’m excited to pursue more ventures, assist more people into homes and most importantly never lose the drive that got me there. Everything happened so quick, it still feels like I’m in a dream. Remembering taking my courses and adamantly stating that I WOULD KILL IT in this game. By 🔥 or force I would get their. To more SUCCESS & MORE LIFE & MORE EQUITY FOR THE CLIENTS❤️

I just want to say CONGRATULATIONS TO THE JOHNSON’S on closing on their second property with me representing them as their agent🤞🏽! This purchase was not easy by any means necessary, we went under contract back in last August  of 2022 and at time as we’re all aware was a different market. Interest rates were extremely lower than the current 6-8% we’re seeing currently at the time I’m writing this. ✅

As we all should know & be prepared for is in case your building a home 6-10+ months out be prepared to be closing in a different atmosphere than when you first contracted. Interest rate goes ⬆️ your pre-approval amount ⬇️. Also, to add insult to injury we were trying to sell his currently property but without enough equity gain, they weren’t expecting to have much of a down payment for the next home which was almost triple their currently home value!

I know I had to pull some strings, make dicey calls and just all around be their to make sure this deal closed. I promised them early on I wasn’t going to fail. I never will call short of that promise with each of my clients! At the end of day, we made it to closing it was all smiles & grins over here! AND AGAIN THE DREAM TEAM DOES IT! Congratulations Daniel & Adeola!❤️🔥 @gr8.wealth @heznadastudios 

p.s. this was the first clients I ever helped purchase a home in my real estate career.

Special thanks to my 🎥 @w1llkombe
